00:03:01.340 --> 00:03:03.860
as this year's speaker and the Charles M.

00:03:03.860 --> 00:03:06.480
and Martha Hitchcock Lecture Series.

00:03:06.480 --> 00:03:09.590
Neil Shubin is a
distinguished paleontologist

00:03:09.590 --> 00:03:11.820
whose research seeks to understand

00:03:11.820 --> 00:03:14.560
the mechanics behind
the evolutionary origin

00:03:14.560 --> 00:03:16.900
of anatomical features of animals.

00:03:16.900 --> 00:03:19.470
His work focuses mainly on the Devonian

00:03:19.470 --> 00:03:21.380
and Triassic periods,

00:03:21.380 --> 00:03:22.350
to understand the pivotal

00:03:22.350 --> 00:03:24.740
ecological and evolutionary shifts

00:03:24.740 --> 00:03:26.920
that occurred during that time.

00:03:26.920 --> 00:03:31.750
In 2004, after scouring the
Canadian Arctic for six years,

00:03:31.750 --> 00:03:35.350
Shubin and his team unearthed
Tiktaalik roseae crae,

00:03:35.350 --> 00:03:39.020
a fossil fishapod, which
despite its fishlike features,

00:03:39.020 --> 00:03:42.930
had a neck, skull,
ribs, and parts of limbs

00:03:42.930 --> 00:03:45.390
similar to land animals.

00:03:45.390 --> 00:03:47.870
This discovery represents the transition

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:50.290
between fish and four-legged mammals

00:03:50.290 --> 00:03:54.330
that occurred over 350 million years ago.

00:03:54.330 --> 00:03:57.650
His announcement about the
discovery of this phenomenon

00:03:57.650 --> 00:04:01.860
on April 6, 2006 in the journal Nature

00:04:01.860 --> 00:04:05.640
made front page news in
newspapers worldwide.

00:04:05.640 --> 00:04:09.260
Finding the 375 million year old fossil

00:04:09.260 --> 00:04:12.120
also spurred Shubin to
write the recent book,

00:04:12.120 --> 00:04:14.480
Your Inner Fish: A Journey Into

00:04:14.480 --> 00:04:18.460
The 3.5-Billion-Year
History Of The Human Body,

00:04:18.460 --> 00:04:20.990
arguing that fish provide an important

00:04:20.990 --> 00:04:23.533
evolutionary step in human history.

00:04:24.380 --> 00:04:29.030
Shubin received his BA from
Columbia University in 1982,

00:04:29.030 --> 00:04:32.050
he earned his PhD from Harvard University

00:04:32.050 --> 00:04:35.830
in Organsimic and
Evolutionary Biology in 1987,

00:04:35.830 --> 00:04:39.290
and in 1996 he was awarded an Honorary MA

00:04:39.290 --> 00:04:41.440
from the University of Pennsylvania.

00:04:41.440 --> 00:04:44.280
He was a Miller postdoctoral
fellow at UC Berkeley

00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:49.030
from 1987 to 1989 and held positions

00:04:49.030 --> 00:04:52.980
as an assistant, associate,
and full professor of biology

00:04:52.980 --> 00:04:56.400
at the University of Pennsylvania
before joining the faculty

00:04:56.400 --> 00:05:00.290
at the University of Chicago in 2000.

00:05:00.290 --> 00:05:03.140
Shubin in currently the Robert R. Bensley

00:05:03.140 --> 00:05:06.920
Professor of Organismal
Biology and Anatomy.

00:05:06.920 --> 00:05:08.550
He serves as the Associate Dean

00:05:08.550 --> 00:05:12.100
of the Biological Sciences
division and as a member

00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:15.083
of the committee on evolutionary biology.

00:05:16.040 --> 00:05:19.440
Shubin has been honored with
a Guggenheim Fellowship,

00:05:19.440 --> 00:05:21.530
the Marcus Singer Award,

00:05:21.530 --> 00:05:23.200
and was named Person of the Week

00:05:23.200 --> 00:05:24.550
by ABC News

00:05:24.550 --> 00:05:27.980
for the week of April 7th, 2006.

00:05:27.980 --> 00:05:30.980
In addition, he has appeared
on the Colbert Report

00:05:30.980 --> 00:05:33.270
and Public Radio International.

