you could find fossils that have a series

00:53:56.800 --> 00:53:59.667
of transitional features
leading to whales,

00:53:59.667 --> 00:54:02.780
devise a family tree well
supported by characteristics

00:54:02.780 --> 00:54:05.170
which show how this sequence
of changes happened.

00:54:05.170 --> 00:54:08.460
And again the major fossils
that support this transformation

00:54:08.460 --> 00:54:10.200
discovered in the last 20 years.

00:54:10.200 --> 00:54:11.840
And the same thing is true with the shift

00:54:11.840 --> 00:54:14.117
from reptiles to mammals,

00:54:14.117 --> 00:54:17.120
to the evolution of our
own species Homo Sapiens

00:54:17.120 --> 00:54:18.610
from our primate relatives,

00:54:18.610 --> 00:54:20.200
from birds to dinosaurs,

00:54:20.200 --> 00:54:23.040
when underlying all these
transformations is this,

00:54:23.040 --> 00:54:25.068
that some of the most important
fossils and understanding

00:54:25.068 --> 00:54:27.450
the great transitions
in the history of life,

00:54:27.450 --> 00:54:29.680
have been discovered in the last 30 years.

00:54:29.680 --> 00:54:31.750
and when you think about this field,

00:54:31.750 --> 00:54:32.840
these are the great times

00:54:32.840 --> 00:54:34.750
in understanding great transformations.

00:54:34.750 --> 00:54:36.810
Nowhere has it become
easier to find fossils

00:54:36.810 --> 00:54:37.650
from around the world,

00:54:37.650 --> 00:54:39.780
to analyze them in new
ways with new imaging

00:54:39.780 --> 00:54:41.460
and new quantitative techniques,

00:54:41.460 --> 00:54:44.540
to study living creatures
with understanding their genes

00:54:44.540 --> 00:54:47.660
and genomes and sequencing
in an ever rapid clip,

00:54:47.660 --> 00:54:50.910
to understand the the
genes that build bodies,

00:54:50.910 --> 00:54:52.200
and control development,

00:54:52.200 --> 00:54:54.830
to understand the
biomechanics of the features

00:54:54.830 --> 00:54:57.690
that these creatures
use to walk and to live,

00:54:57.690 --> 00:54:58.927
to understand the ecosystems

00:54:58.927 --> 00:55:01.300
and the systems that
function as ecosystems

00:55:01.300 --> 00:55:02.350
and the food webs,

00:55:02.350 --> 00:55:05.110
the ways these creatures
would have interacted.

00:55:05.110 --> 00:55:08.300
Nowhere, at no other time in
the history of our science

00:55:08.300 --> 00:55:10.870
has it been a better time to
study the great transformations

00:55:10.870 --> 00:55:13.570
because this is now a
fundamentally integrative field,

00:55:13.570 --> 00:55:14.970
and an integrative biology.

00:55:14.970 --> 00:55:15.852
Thank you very much.

00:55:15.852 --> 00:55:19.019
(audience applauding)

